      <solution>
        <title>Written Solution</title>
        <p> (a) The y-intercept occurs at <m>f(0)=0</m>. Setting <m>f(x)=0</m> and solving for <m>x</m>, we find that <m>x=0</m> is the only <m>x</m>-intercept. 
